
[1]thrash

   THRASH, v.t.

   1. To beat out grain from the husk or pericarp with a flail; as, to
   thrash wheat, rye or oats.

   2. To beat corn off from the cob or spike; as, to thrash maiz.

   3. To beat soundly with a stick or whip; to drub.

       THRASH, v.i. To practice thrashing; to perform the business of
                   thrashing; as a man who thrashes well.

   1. To labor; to drudge.

   I rather would be Mevius, thrash for rhymes,

   Like his, the scorn and scandal of the times--
